Abstract:  Introduction:  angioedemas are a frequent cause of consultation in allergology. A small number of cases imply a diagnostic and therapeutic challenge and involve transfusion medicine.  Objective:  to outline the clinical presentation and handling of a patient with hereditary angioedema.  Method:  presentation of the clinical case including personal and family history, as well as a description and account of the conditionâ€™s challenge with the contribution of updated scientific literature.  Results:  ways of approaching the condition in clinical, paraclinical, therapeutic and prophylactic terms, based on the study of a case.  Conclusions:  the study managed to address this rather unusual and not well known condition, with the prospect of diagnostic and therapeutic improvement for the quality of life of these patients.